premise_source_doc_sentence: Bahrain Island  (  جزيرة البحرين Jazīrah al-Baḥrayn  )  , also known as al-Awal Island and formerly as Bahrein , is the largest island within the archipelago of Bahrain , and forms the bulk of the country 's land mass while hosting the majority of its population .
Muharraq Island , formerly known as Moharek , is the second largest island in the archipelago of Bahrain after Bahrain Island .
Bahrain 's population is 1,234,571  (  c. 2010  )  , including 666,172 non-nationals .
Ares was also worshipped by the country 's indigenous and Greek population .

It is an island country consisting of a small archipelago centered around Bahrain Island , situated between the Qatar peninsula and the north eastern coast of Saudi Arabia , to which it is connected by the 25 km King Fahd Causeway .
It lies off the north western corner of Bahrain Island , near Budaiya village , and east of Jidda Island , located in Persian Gulf .
